addNftToCollection(uint256,uint256).notice: This method adds an nft into the collection, i.e. it adds the tokenId of the NFT to the nftIds array of the collection and increments the nftCount.

constructor.notice: The deployed NFT contract's address is provided as a parameter in the constructor,  in order to create an instance.

createCollection(string,string,string,st.notice: This method creates a collection, increments the collectionCount accordingly, generates a new collectionID for it,  and adds it to the allCollections array.
This method creates a collection, increments the collectionCount accordingly, generates a new collectionID for it,  and adds it to the allCollections array.

deleteCollection(uint256).notice: This method deletes a collection, decrements the collectionCount and  removes it from the idToIndex mapping.

getAllCollectionsByOwnerAddress(address).notice: This method returns a list of all the collections owned by the provided address.

getNftIdsByCollectionId(uint256).notice: This method returns an array containing the tokenIds of all the NFTs  that are present in the collection.

getOwnerByCollectionId(uint256).notice: This method returns the address of the respective collection.

listCollection(address,uint256).notice: This method sets the isListed field of the collection to be true, i.e. it lists the  collection to the marketplace.

removeNftFromCollection(uint256,uint256).notice: This method removes the provided nft from the collection, i.e. it finds the index at which the nft is stored, removes it and decrements the value of nftCount.

setMarketplaceContractAddress(address).notice: This method sets the marketplace contract address for super admin validations. This method is called for the first time when the marketplace contract is created, and  can be called again but only by the super admin itself.

unlistCollection(address,uint256).notice: This method sets the isListed field of the collection to be false, i.e. it unlists the  collection from the marketplace.

userdoc.notice: This contract stores the details of collections defined by the Definitions smart contract, which  includes collection id, name, description, owner's name, owner's address, number of nfts, category, etc
